OL,3,CMurder victim's mum in Westminster for
OL,4,Ccrucial stage of fight to change law
OL,6,FIt was the idea of Olivia's mum Cheryl
OL,7,FKorbel, who was appalled when her
OL,8,Fdaughter's killer, Thomas Cashman,
OL,9,Frefused to leave his cell when he was
OL,10,Fsentenced to 42 years at Manchester
OL,11,FCrown Court.
OL,13,FThe hope is that tougher sanctions
OL,14,Fcould be introduced in similar
OL,15,Fsituations, including more jail time
OL,16,For loss of privileges in prison.
OL,18,FThe measures would be included in the
OL,19,FGovernment's Victims and Courts Bill,
OL,20,Fwhich is having its second reading in
OL,21,FParliament.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
