OL,3,CMurder victim's mum in Westminster for
OL,4,Ccrucial stage of fight to change law
OL,6,FThe MP for Knowsley, Annalise Midgley,
OL,7,Fsaid in the Commons: " Nothing in this
OL,8,Fworld can bring Olivia back. But
OL,9,Finstead of collapsing under this
OL,10,Fweight, Cheryl fought back.
OL,12,F"She and her family have campaigned -
OL,13,Fso no other family will suffer the
OL,14,Fsame.
OL,16,F"Olivia's Law is her work. It is
OL,17,FOlivia's legacy. It is Cheryl's legacy.
OL,19,F"Olivia's Law is a simple change: Give
OL,20,Fjudges the power to compel offenders
OL,21,Fto attend their sentencing hearings.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
