OL,6,FIf they refuse, there are consequences
OL,7,F- real and proportionate sanctions;
OL,8,Flimiting privileges like visitation or
OL,9,Ftime out of cell.
OL,11,F"Cheryl fought hard for that principle
OL,12,F` that refusal should carry
OL,13,Fconsequences. Without it, the law
OL,14,Fwould lack the strength it needs."
